---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Section 75 Claim Pack"
  description="A £6.99 plain-English PDF workbook for making a Section 75 claim. Includes a claim letter, evidence checklist, rejection rebuttal templates, and a Financial Ombudsman complaint template."
  disclaimer={true}
>
  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">

    <h1>Section 75 Claim Pack</h1>

    <p>
      Banks sometimes reject Section 75 claims because the evidence is unclear, the wrong process is used, or the claim is not explained properly. This pack helps you present the key facts clearly from the start, and gives you the letters you need if the bank pushes back.
    </p>

    <!-- Who it is for / not for -->
    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-4 text-sm text-gray-700">
        <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Who this pack is for</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">This pack is for you if:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside marker:text-green-500">
          <li>you paid at least part of a purchase on a personal credit card;</li>
          <li>the total price was more than £100 and no more than £30,000;</li>
          <li>the retailer has failed to deliver, gone bust, refused a refund, or supplied faulty or not-as-described goods;</li>
          <li>you want to write the claim yourself instead of using a claims company.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-sm text-gray-700">
        <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Who this pack is not for</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">This pack may not be suitable if:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside marker:text-gray-400">
          <li>you paid by debit card only;</li>
          <li>the purchase was under £100;</li>
          <li>the purchase was made on a company credit card;</li>
          <li>you want someone to handle the claim for you;</li>
          <li>your case is already in court or involves a very large or complex dispute.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
      <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">What this product is — and is not</p>
      <p class="mb-1">We are not a claims management company. We do not handle claims, contact banks, negotiate with card providers, or represent customers. We provide general information and downloadable template documents only.</p>
      <p>This website provides general information and templates. It is not legal advice. <a href="/disclaimer/" class="underline hover:text-gray-800">Full disclaimer</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="not-prose my-6">
      <a
        href="https://buy.stripe.com/fZucN5cKu1Kf9VK0hwes000"
        class="btn-primary-lg"
      >
        Buy the claim pack — £6.99
      </a>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">PDF format. Readable on any device. No subscription.</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400">Digital download: by buying, you agree to immediate access and understand your 14-day cancellation right ends once the download starts. If the link or file does not work, <a href="/contact/" class="underline">contact us</a> and we will fix it or send a replacement.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>What's inside the PDF</h2>

    <p>A single plain-English PDF workbook. It walks you through your claim from start to finish, with the letters and templates you need at each stage.</p>

  </article>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
    {[
      { title: 'Start-here guide',           desc: 'What Section 75 is and how to use this pack' },
      { title: 'Section 75 checker',         desc: 'Confirm your purchase qualifies before you write' },
      { title: 'Claim details worksheet',    desc: 'A form to capture the key facts of your case' },
      { title: 'Evidence checklist',         desc: 'Know exactly what to gather and send' },
      { title: 'Initial claim letter',       desc: 'Ready-to-send template citing the legislation' },
      { title: 'Chase message',              desc: 'Follow up if the bank does not reply in time' },
      { title: 'Rebuttal templates',         desc: 'Counter the most common bank rejection reasons' },
      { title: 'FOS complaint letter',       desc: 'Use this if the bank refuses or goes silent' },
      { title: 'Glossary and sources',       desc: 'Plain-English definitions and official links' },
    ].map(({ title, desc }) => (
      <div class="rounded border-l-4 bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3 text-sm" style="border-left-color: #1e3a5f;">
        <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-0.5">{title}</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500">{desc}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">

    <h2>What it costs and how to get it</h2>

    <p>
      The claim pack costs <strong>£6.99</strong> as a one-off download. No subscription. No auto-renewal. You pay once, and the files are yours.
    </p>

    <p>
      Payment is handled securely by Stripe. After payment you are taken immediately to a download page where you can save the PDF. Stripe will also send a payment receipt to the email address you used at checkout.
    </p>

    <div class="not-prose my-6">
      <a
        href="https://buy.stripe.com/fZucN5cKu1Kf9VK0hwes000"
        class="btn-primary-lg"
      >
        Buy the claim pack — £6.99
      </a>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">PDF format. Readable on any device. No subscription.</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400">Digital download: by buying, you agree to immediate access and understand your 14-day cancellation right ends once the download starts. If the link or file does not work, <a href="/contact/" class="underline">contact us</a> and we will fix it or send a replacement.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>What happens after payment</h2>

    <ol>
      <li>Pay securely through the Stripe checkout.</li>
      <li>After payment you are taken to a download page. Save the PDF somewhere easy to find — you may need it over the coming weeks.</li>
      <li>Open the PDF and start at the beginning — the start-here guide and checker will confirm which letter applies to your situation.</li>
      <li>Fill in the highlighted placeholders in your chosen letter with your own details.</li>
      <li>Send the completed letter and supporting evidence to your card provider's disputes team.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Is this legal advice?</h2>

    <p>
      No. The claim pack contains template letters and general guidance, not legal advice for your specific situation. If your case is complex, the amount at stake is large, or you have already been through the Financial Ombudsman process without success, you should consider consulting a solicitor who specialises in consumer law.
    </p>

    <p>
      For most standard Section 75 disputes involving administration, non-delivery, or goods not as described, the templates in this pack are sufficient to make a well-structured claim without professional help.
    </p>

    <h2>Refund policy</h2>

    <p>
      Because this is a digital download, you may be asked at checkout to agree to immediate access and confirm that you understand your cancellation right is lost once the download starts. If there is a technical problem with the file or download link, <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> and we will fix it or provide a replacement copy.
    </p>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
